The night Aaron died I spiraled so hard that I texted the crisis hotline. I ended up canceling it because it took so long to get connected with someone but I think that’s because it was so late at night. I still think it’s a good idea especially for people who get phone anxiety

Headspace can also be beneficial. I haven’t used it specifically for depression or anxiety but I HAVE used it to fall asleep when my anxiety was too high to do by myself. I’m not sure if they have a free option but they do offer a pretty good student discount. it’s worth it.
Both are incredibly easy and free to use. You can choose different activities you think will help to distract until the wave is over. I like it a lot.

There are 2 apps in the AppStore right now that I’ve used to help when i get the urge to hurt myself or am so down in the dumps I cant pull myself out. Calm Harm and Calm fear (both by the same company). Calm harm is geared toward managing self harm urges; fear is for anxiety.
